            <thetext>It could be possible to completely erase qx.core.Variant.select expressions in 
optimized code, even if the variant variable in question is not in the current 
variant set. Currently, if a variant variable is not mentioned in the current 
variant set, the calls to qx.core.Variant.select can be left in the code. (One 
such case is when the variant set is completely empty; then, the original 
source tree is used, with all containing qx.core.Variant.select calls). - This 
seems unnecessary. It has to be clarified whether a qx.core.Variant.select map 
has to always provide a &#39;default&#39; case, or otherwise what the semantics are if 
a variant variable is not set at all.</thetext>
